    <p>{`The Vector `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`concat`}</inlineCode>{` transform
accepts and outputs `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/about/data-model/log/"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`log`}</inlineCode></a>{` events, allowing you to concat
(substrings) of other fields to a new one.`}</p>
    {
      /*
          THIS FILE IS AUTOGENERATED!
           To make changes please edit the template located at:
           website/docs/reference/transforms/concat.md.erb
      */
    }
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "configuration"
    }}>{`Configuration`}</h2>
    <Tabs block={true} defaultValue="common" values={[{
      "label": "Common",
      "value": "common"
    }, {
      "label": "Advanced",
      "value": "advanced"
    }]} mdxType="Tabs">
      <TabItem value="common" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-toml",
            "metastring": "title=\"vector.toml\"",
            "title": "\"vector.toml\""
          }}>{`[transforms.my_transform_id]
  type = "concat" # required
  inputs = ["my-source-or-transform-id"] # required
  items = ["first[..3]", "second[-5..]", "third[3..6]"] # required
  target = "root_field_name" # required
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="advanced" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-toml",
            "metastring": "title=\"vector.toml\"",
            "title": "\"vector.toml\""
          }}>{`[transforms.my_transform_id]
  type = "concat" # required
  inputs = ["my-source-or-transform-id"] # required
  items = ["first[..3]", "second[-5..]", "third[3..6]"] # required
  joiner = " " # optional, default
  target = "root_field_name" # required
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
    </Tabs>
    <Fields filters={true} mdxType="Fields">
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={[["first[..3]", "second[-5..]", "third[3..6]"]]} groups={[]} name={"items"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"[string]"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "items"
        }}>{`items`}</h3>
        <p>{`A list of substring definitons in the format of source_field`}{`[start..end]`}{`. For
both start and end negative values are counted from the end of the string.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={false} defaultValue={" "} enumValues={null} examples={[" ", ",", "_", "+"]} groups={[]} name={"joiner"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "joiner"
        }}>{`joiner`}</h3>
        <p>{`The string that is used to join all items.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["root_field_name", "parent.child", "array[0]"]} groups={[]} name={"target"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "target"
        }}>{`target`}</h3>
        <p>{`The name for the new label.
See `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "#field-notation-syntax"
          }}>{`Field Notation Syntax`}</a>{` for more info.`}</p>
      </Field>
    </Fields>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "examples"
    }}>{`Examples`}</h2>
    <p>{`Given the following input log event:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-json"
      }}>{`{
  "message": "Hello world",
  "month": "12",
  "day": "25",
  "year": "2020"
}
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`And the following example configuration:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-toml"
      }}>{`[transforms.concat_date]
  type = "concat"
  items = ["month", "day", "year"]
  target = "date"
  joiner = "/"
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`A log event will be output with the following structure:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-json"
      }}>{`{
  "message": "Hello world",
  "date": "12/25/2020", // <-- new field
  "month": "12",
  "day": "25",
  "year": "2020"
}
`}</code></pre>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "how-it-works"
    }}>{`How It Works`}</h2>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "complex-processing"
    }}>{`Complex Processing`}</h3>
    <p>{`If you encounter limitations with the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`concat`}</inlineCode>{`
transform then we recommend using a `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://vector.dev/components/?functions%5B%5D=program"
      }}>{`runtime transform`}</a>{`.
These transforms are designed for complex processing and give you the power of
full programming runtime.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "environment-variables"
    }}>{`Environment Variables`}</h3>
    <p>{`Environment variables are supported through all of Vector's configuration.
Simply add `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`\${MY_ENV_VAR}`}</inlineCode>{` in your Vector configuration file and the variable
will be replaced before being evaluated.`}</p>
    <p>{`You can learn more in the
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/setup/configuration/#environment-variables"
      }}>{`Environment Variables`}</a>{` section.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "field-notation-syntax"
    }}>{`Field Notation Syntax`}</h3>
    <p>{`The `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#target"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`target`}</inlineCode></a>{` options
support `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/reference/field-path-notation/"
      }}>{`Vector's field notation syntax`}</a>{`,
enabling access to root-level, nested, and array field values. For example:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-toml",
        "metastring": "title=\"vector.toml\"",
        "title": "\"vector.toml\""
      }}>{`[transforms.my_concat_transform_id]
  # ...
  target = "root_field_name"
  target = "parent.child"
  target = "array[0]"
  # ...
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`You can learn more about Vector's field notation in the
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/reference/field-path-notation/"
      }}>{`field notation reference`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    </MDXLayout>;
}

